Description

ZRL 2022/23 Season: Round 1 - Race: 6 of 6

The 170+ community divisions, 1,800 teams and 14,000 racers are organized and managed by our partners over at WTRL. All Zwift Racing League events are invite only and you'll need to join one of the many existing teams if you want to join in on the fun. Check out all the details, see the full schedule, rules and even find a team at WTRL's website - www.WTRL.racing. WTRL is looking forward to welcoming you to the ZRL and WTRL community.

A selection of ZRL races are also broadcast live throughout race days on Zwift Community Live. Follow along, or perhaps even be a featured racer, at www.youtube.com/c/ZwiftCommunityLive.

Check out ZwiftInsider (www.zwiftinsider.com) for some great course previews and very funny articles written by ZRL'ers about their experiences in the biggest cycling eSports league in the world!

Want to check out the race route ahead of time?
There are many community recon-rides that you can join without a team and these are a great place to find a team too. Zwift run hourly Zwift Racing League Recon Rides on Mondays that feature the same course that everyone will race the next day. Check out www.zwift.com/events/tag/zrlrecon for a full list.

RIDE ON!

WTRL Website: www.WTRL.racing
ZRL Facebook Page: www.facebook.com/groups/wtrlzwiftracingleague
